Why does my login fail when I use the ltpa-usrnm attribute? You use a Domino server as your LDAP, and the login attribute you want to use is ltpa-usrnm. This is acceptable, as the login attribute can be set accordingly in the wimconfig.xml. When the search string is built for the login, it is in the form, cn=username, o=orgname.

This cause the following exception to the returned:

[3/30/16 9:56:03:453 CDT] 000000f7 exception E com.ibm.ws.wim.adapter.ldap.LdapConnection getAttributes CWWIM4520E The 'javax.naming.InvalidNameException: "CN=username/O=orgname": [LDAP: error code 34 - Invalid DN Syntax]; remaining name '"CN=username/O=orgname'";

